<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=98995398618700></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98995398618700><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98995398618700>Go For the DE!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98995398618700#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=44334><span id=Scholar>ThePhantazm</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>19 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 15th 3:13 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp; A few months ago, I decided that I wanted to start a cleric. My options were Gnome, Dwarf, High Elf, Human, Dark Elf, Euridite, and maybe Halfling and Half Elf. I was also well aware how many clerics were High Elfs and Dwarfs. Frankly, High Elfs have better starting stats, and dwarfs tend to be easy to play.<br><br>I chose to play a dark elf. Why?<br><br>1. Dark Elves look hell a cool.<br>2. Evil classes and races need more healers.<br>3. Starting stats are nice.<br>4. You get HIDE which will save your life if you are in a dangerous place and are still LFG.<br>5. VI has put in a few DE items that make being a DE a little easier.<br><br>Hard part. The faction makes you KOS in a lot of norath. Banking sucks, and long trips to find a merchant that will sell to you also sucks. If you have played "good race/classes", you may not be able to play in the same areas you have before.<br><br>I suggest these zones for theses levels.<br><br>(1-6) Nektulos forest; newbie crap<br>(6-10) West commons; at orc camps<br>(10-13) East commons; Kodiaks, and Skells in Befallen<br>(13-18) Oasis; crocks and orcs<br>(19-28) Lake of Ill Omen; sarnaks and everything else<br>(29-39) The Overthere; everything (there is a bank and merchants for DE here)<br>(39-45) The Dreadlands; group at Nwall<br>(46- ) ?<br><br>I hope you chose to play a DE, it may be a little harder at times, but deffinetly worth it. If you are not a DE, the lvl/zone thing should aply to you too. Cleric Power!!<br><br>Becursed into Darkness<br>42nd Sphere of Innoruuk's hate<br>Member of the Scarlet Underground<br>in the land of Terris-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
