	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I won't answer to "Wise One" but I have a level 19 DE Cleric anI can say I have had no problems at all, in fact I have had it easier than alot of High Elf Clerics I know.<br><br>First you have the same starting WIS as the Dwarf but a little less STR, but STR is an easy fix at low levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;The HIE does not have a significant WIS edge on you at this level and with equipment selection it never will matter.<br><br>My WIS at level 19 is 176, and I'm still wearing Moonstone Rings (yes I'm a 'little twinked').  WIS items are plentiful for Clerics.  Adamantite Epolets at about 200pp are the best investment you will ever make.<br><br>Weight, this is the difference between you and the Dwarf.  The way around it, never wear Bronze armor, never.  Start with the standard patchwork, leather, whatever you can afford.  Once you have money get a Dwarven Ringmail Tunic (12AC, 25pp), Sarnak Emb(???) Tabord (14 AC, 50pp) or best bet Charred Guardian Breastplate (16AC +3 STR).  Other slots:  waiste Thick Banded Belt (8AC wt1), Purity Belt (5AC +2 STR), Neck Orc Fang Necklace (5AC +3 STR), Chipped Velium Amulet (4AC +2 STR, +20 hit points)<br><br>Alot of your spots will be jewlry at low levels which weight almost nothing.  The Silver Ruby Veil has +4WIS +4STR again helps weight.<br><br>We have a good starting area, it will get you to level 8 easy.  You then play in the commons till 14 or so then hit Oasis like the rest.  At level 18 you then shot past all good races with XP by heading to the Overthere.  At lvl 18/19 everytime I stand up and anounce my presence I have at least 2 tells asking me to group.  I usually get both to join me and make a bigger group, and we kill non stop.  There are few healers in OT and you will be well taken care of.<br><br>Dark Elves are good Clerics.  I think they make much better clerics than High Elves with the better strength and stamina.  Dwarves may be agruably better Clerics, but everyone sees Dwarf Clerics.  For a little loss in strength and stamina I'm somewhat unique and can hunt different zones without faction loss.<br><br>Play any of the three, but if you are thinking about a Dark Elf, I think you will like it.<br><br>Vildaar<br>lvl 19 DE Cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
