	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, a DE Cleric is absolutely feasible, but will be very difficult.&nbsp;&nbsp;A bit more so than a high elf anyway.  The reason there are so many HIE Clerics is the Wis.  High Elves have spectacular starting WIS, but low strength.  <br>My main is a Dwarven Cleric, lvl 30 now.  Since Clerics can wear plate armor, you will need a decent strength if you are to carry your armor and a decent bit of loot.  This is why so many Dorf Clerics; decent starting Strength and Wisdom.  More than enough of both to get you through.  I'm pretty certain I will be able to get 200 wis before planer levels (46+). <br>Anyway, when I made my Cleric, I had very limited game knowledge, and if I had known then how many Dwarven Clerics there are out there, I probably would have chosen a different race for him.<br>Dark elves definitely have a respectable wisdom, but your strength WILL suffer, unless you throw all your points into it, then your wis will suffer.  =\  If you dump everything into wis, and whatever is extra into strength, you'll have about 70 str with a DE.  <br>My Dwarf's equipment, including backpacks and some food, all comes out to about 74 stones.  So, that is why a DE cleric would be so difficult, combined with the faction problems.  <br>Just my 2cp.  =)<br><br>Jarochai Alabaster, 30th Dwarven Cleric<br>Arogati, 10th Human Necromancer<br>Tordara, 10th Barbarian Rogue<br>Ethemos, 8th Iksar Monk<br>Drusydia, 9th Iksar Shaman<br><br>...I have too many alts...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
